-- Chaowei Power Sets Price of Hong Kong Initial Offer Shares at HK$2.18 Each
-- Stanley James
-- 2010-07-05T22:30:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/chaowei-power-sets-price-of-hong-kong-initial-offer-shares-at-hk-2-18-each.html

          
          
             Chaowei Power Holdings Ltd. set the
price of shares in its Hong Kong public offering at HK$2.18, the
lower end of the range it announced earlier, the company said in
a statement to the Hong Kong stock exchange today. Net proceeds
from the share sale will be about HK$474.8 million, according to
the statement. The company said last month that it will offer
250 million shares at HK$2.18 to HK$2.90 each in the IPO.
Trading in the shares is expected to start July 7, according to
the statement.  
          
          


  


        